social_posts.post_text: Gotta always recount the “Ebenezer [moments] saying, Hitherto hath the LORD helped us.” 1 Sam 7:12

Listen, this is a big week coming up for us. Was scrolling as I’m juggling literal universes, and came across this clip of me directing a multicam broadcast from a couple of years ago. 

To those that know, on a regular scale, this is a no-no— or at least the less ideal nature. The tech director (switcher), shouldn’t be calling the shots. They just switch. The director calls. I’m grateful that no matter the environment or budget, I’m not so sophisticated that I’ve forgotten how to get the job done by any means necessary. And that. That’s what this week is about. If your praying with us 🙌🏾, sending good vibes 🤞🏾, or positive energy 👌🏾 drop something in the comments.

#ProfessorPowell: I haven’t posted many student interactions this semester, cause I figured out how to weed out the 💩 early in the semester (We’ll see how it closes). This was my last transmission to one of my courses last night.

Whenever I share good news with my team at @newbirthmbc the revive this video. In gospel music there’s a tail of a song called a drive or a vamp. The background repeats something over and over and the lead singer has the duty to ad lib over it. It’s like pointed jazz. Well @janaedenisee is one of my personal favorites. I started directing the choir when I was 12 and I love when a lead singer follows my cue 🤣🤣🤣. So on this “Thank you” vamp that @_ashtonjaxon started, Nae got it and I tossed “It coulda been me.” Lyrics from a totally different song and tempo and when she took it, joy over took me 😂😂. Let this be an amalgamation of lessons. 1. Good leaders can handle a joke and welcome it for rapport. 2. Never let go of the things you’ve polished over the years, it’ll come back somehow. 3. Don’t forget to say thanks when you’ve received something you didn’t deserve.
AMAZING day of pitches. Y’all ain’t ready. Grateful for the village. More later.
One can go faster, two can go further. Dream with someone.
My body is at the house but my mind is still in Haiti a month ago. Our two other vacations this year are already warranted. Just in the last month alone. 🫠😂😂
You gotta watch til you see the frogs 🤣🤣🤣 Todays post is just a day-in-the-life. To know my boys is to love them. 🫠🫠🤣🤣
Share this with the creatives you love to let them know they aren’t slow, it’s just simmering. We gotta learn to embrace the ideas that need to brew. Can you relate or am I alone?!
Get the validation how you need it. Honestly. As creatives we all need it from somewhere. Whether without or within. Send to a creative you see.

Adulting and parenting is nothing but an endless string of “if it ain’t one thing, it’s another”.

@vincentpowell and I had quite the Murphy’s Law day yesterday. On the list of damages was one of the shelves in our boys’ room randomly falling and crashing to the floor…waking up a sleeping toddler, denting one of the floor planks, and shattering my beloved @tiffanyandco piggy bank that was gifted to them. Ughhh! We managed to stay level headed picking up every single dime, quarter, nickel, penny, and dollar…so maybe that’s the silver lining?

Aye God, I ain’t gon hold you, but whatever you’re working out…some cliff notes would be dope😂

#adultingishard
There will never be another. Better than all the rest.
Captivating. Charismatic. Show stopping. I was as fascinated with her and her career as I was with Michael Jackson’s or James Brown’s. Artistry at every turn.

She’s 70 in slide one and 60 in slide two. I used to watch Tina and MJ European concerts as a kid on VHS over and over. Charisma. Showmanship. Magnetism. Plenty of artists have built shows with a moving apparatus or flying part of the stage that moves over the audience, but even Michael Jackson needed a stunt double and distracting gimmicks Show me one with the talent RUNNING back and forth with no safety harness and working a STADIUM to their core, while the stage arm is moving and you’d only be talking about Tina. Only.
Every time I talk Imma talk about story. Story is king. It drives us. I teach it. I talk it. I do it.
Grateful for the boys who call me dad, the woman I made them with, and the men we call dad who help keep our world in orbit. Happy Father’s Day. Thinking of the ones who are no longer with us today.

Babe. 

During those moments when you doubt your abilities, strength, or decisions as a parent of two amazing Black boys, I hope you turn to this treasure trove of memories. Let them serve as a reminder that you are more than enough, capable, and deserving of all the love you receive. We adore you, Bubb.

You deserve a higher ground…
#happyfathersday

The new @reddigitalcinema #KomodoX production model started shipping today, and for the first time in history I was one of the few to touch a pre-release RED camera. [ @instajarred I’m patiently wait for my special Bronze edition 😎— I know you’re just waiting for my first $200M box office hit, standby.]

I got to battle test it 2 weeks ago thanks to our friend Darren Fordham, over RED Broadcast Cinema Accounts. 

We put it against the #OGKomodo, #VRaptorS35 (which I LOVE), the #VRaptorVV, and the #VRaptorXL to compare it at @newbirth. It was a shootout of the gods. 

We put all of that against our current URSA’s set up and there was no question at all. There’s only one kind of cinematic broadcast and RED is making it cheaper by the day!

The RKX is beefed up a bit from the #OGKomodo. The KOMODO-X is capabale of recording in 6K 17:9 / R3D ELQ at 80fps, and 4K at up to 120fps. As a comparison, the OGK was only capable of recording up to 40fps 6K 17:9 (6144 X 3240) in REDCODE HQ, MQ and L. RKX also comes with a built in v-mount, a better monitor solution which actually leaves a spare SDI out, and better dynamic range than the OG.

We’ll be grabbing an assortment of the above listed bodies at NB soon, to completely thrust us into a different stratosphere. @jamalhbryant told y’all Sunday: You Gon Learn Today.

*whispers* I’m also selling my OGKomodo to buy the new Production RED Komodo X but don’t tell @blackglass.

Yo, the rubber has met the road. This is what the strike means for SAG members. I’m certain the general public will feel this more than they feel the limitations and absence of WGA members. These are defining moments and I’m fighting with and for the people with the true power, the heart, the craft, the art. The writers and actors. Other unions need to get clear on whose side they are on. Cc: @iamtwinkiebyrd

Yo. The “Diamond Finder” @iamtwinkiebyrd is a diamond herself. Last night she shared with my grad production class at @texassouthern. We talked for 4+hrs students stories and her personal anecdotes about everything from walking in rooms uninvited and proving you belong there, to the revolutionary impact of old music videos on modern storytelling, to her special approach when accepting a new project. What a journey. So patient. So kind. So giving. Thanks Twinkie ❤️

The past few weeks have been full of highs and lows. I would say I’ll tell you about it, but I’ll be busy in 5min and forget. Lol

One thing keeps me sane. Our hands lifted up. Our mouth filled with praise. A heart of thanksgiving. What you can’t see is @blackglass rubbing my back as we sang and worshiped. Knowing that my weak, frail, vulnerable self is still covered by her humbles me so much. Saw this video of Elder Goldwire singing one of my favorite hymns “It Is Well” (other two are What A Friend & In The Garden) and I wept severely. “Whatever my lot.” 

Thanks for snapping this one @larrywilliamsphotos. Means a lot.

I’m one of the most talented directors you know, but I’m only as popular as you make me. Share this.

Wishing my bride and my best friend @blackglass the heartiest, happiest birthday. 

Each year with you is a journey richer in love, laughter, and wisdom. You’re the rock of our family and the light in my life, shining brighter with every passing year.
Here’s to the woman who brings joy and strength into our lives every day. Your grace and resilience inspire me, and our sons adore you more than words can express. We’re blessed to call you ours. 

To more adventures, endless love, and shared dreams. Happy Birthday, my love! ❤️🌟 #HappyBirthday #QueenOfOurHearts #MoreThanJustADay #BlessedAndGrateful
